    "body": "### Problem\n\nError \"Invalid range\" if you visual select something and do cbuffer. Passing a single number like 1cb works.\r\nBug also in upstream https://github.com/vim/vim/issues/14638 but the suggested patch is for a file that no longer exists in neovim (and I couldn't make it work by modyfing ex_cmds.lua addr_type to ADDR_LINES for cgetbuffer\r\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\r\nwrite something\r\nselect it\r\n:'<,'>cbuffer\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nCbuffer should take visual range (at least that's my expectation reading that cbuffer can take ranges)\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n v0.10.0-dev-2898+g4c31a1b80 (same on v0.9.5)\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes 8.2.212 reproductible on master too\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nwindows 11 (wsl2 ubuntu 22.04)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwindows terminal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage for 0.9.5 compilation for master",
